<!channel>: For various reasons, we haven’t been able to run through a successful demo all week. Senior management has some serious concern regarding our ability to deliver for our client on this project, and we need to be able to gain their confidence tomorrow. Furthermore, we’ve put a ton of work into this project, but fumbling through a broken demo undermines all of that hard work. I appreciate things are under construction at this point, but from here on out what we show on the wall every morning (and at other demos) has to be rock-solid. To that end:

* If it’s not running on the wall, it’s not done.
* No known-broken code in /dev. Period. Do not push if changes have not been tested on the wall. 
* We will continue to load and test nightlies in advance of the 9:15 check. If the build is broken, we roll back to the last good one and show that at our demo time.
* We will review the updated cubby welcome flow tomorrow at 9:15. <@U11JK4QSK> If you know you can get the welcome cubby flow done by 9am tomorrow morning, then edit in the template. Otherwise, you need to work in the “test” template and we need to roll back the live one to the last known-good before you started editing.
I’ll be in before 9 tomorrow to check everything out so we have enough time to trigger a Jenkins build if needed.
